texts.text: >You defeat Vishnu's demon minions!
How wretched.
Beaten by a few measly Dx2s...
Low-level demons really are worthless! I'll show you true power.
Here comes a boss fight!
No way we're losin' now!
Let's go, y'all!
I will fight with you!
>As Vishnu steps forward, everyone confronts him together.
>The battle intensifies.
>Or so one would expect—
*Grunt*
*Groan*
The Liberators' fierce attacks swiftly bring Vishnu to his knees.
H-How...? It makes no sense...
Yeah, this IS weird.
This is freakin' Vishnu.
How the hell did we overpower him?
"Vishnu," huh?
Not much of a "supreme god," is he?
...What did you say?
You dare question whether I'm the real Vishnu?
You there, human! What did you say?!
No one insults me!
You'll pay for your insolence with death!
*Shout*
>Trembling with rage, Vishnu opens his arms and looks to the sky.
O Great Aura Gate, my Creator!
Hear my plea and grant me more powerful magic!
I am Vishnu!
>The ground shakes violently.
*Yell*
*Shout*
White mist starts to seep from nearby demons.
>It flows toward Vishnu and envelops him.
Don't tell me he's stealin' power from his toadies?!
Still, I believe this smoke is...
*Groan*
Oh? What am I doing here?
It would seem everyone's sanity has returned.
"Sanity"...? Ugh, I can't take any more of that smoke!
Whenever we inhale it, Vishnu works us to the bone!
>The demons make their escape.
As I thought, the demons here were also under his control.
The smoke that brainwashed them was likely Vishnu's own power.
Right. Now that he took it all back, it's time for the main event.
>The Liberators ready themselves for battle.
>The smoke around Vishnu slowly dissipates, and...
Hahahaha! This body overflows with phenomenal power!
Your fun ends here.
You'll rue the day you made a fool of me!
Uh...
Why is there a Chatterskull here?
? My body... What is this...?
Why?! Why did I transform into this low-level demon...?!
>A Chatterskull suddenly appears.
>However, it is apparently the flabbergasted Vishnu.
Yo, what's the deal?
...Again, this is just speculation,
but we might be looking at Vishnu's true form.
What?
The "Unrivaled Conqueror Vishnu" is his ideal form,
which the Aura Gate made a reality.
This Aura Gate
was created to boost his ego and self-esteem...
But although it is an Aura Gate,
to create a demon like Vishnu is no easy task.
So, it only made him LOOK like Vishnu?
Yes. He was granted finite power,
and since he asked for more to fight us...
Any power used to brainwash and keep his form was redirected?
(So, that's why the demons came to their senses)
(and Vishnu transformed back.)
(But that means—)
(He's stronger than ever...!)
>As the Liberators raise their defenses,
>the Chatterskull continues to panic.
Me, a Chatterskull?!
That's impossible! I am without equal!
Every demon kneels before me... I outshine all...
I am the puppet master. Those pathetic chumps are my pawns.
To be on their level...
How could I sink this low...?
...After hearin' all this, I've got just one thing to say.
You hate demons, don't ya?
You're no fan of humans either, but
you don't trust demons one bit.
Hah! "Trust"? Don't make me laugh.
In the end, most demons are mere tools to be used by Dx2s.
Yet those useless pieces of shit can't even protect us!
They're the entire reason I died!
Sorry you took a dirt nap, but don't blame your demon allies.
They're precious partners, not weapons.
"Partners"?
They've got free will and choose to help us Dx2s.
Just like Lost Name here.
We didn't give him any orders.
He's been fightin' with us on his own terms.
This demon is doin' us a favor.
Hahahahaha!
When I was a Dx2, I knew fools like you who said the same thing!
It always gave me the creeps!
...You're all nothin' but talk.
It's time to face reality!
>As Chatterskull shouts, smoke pours out of his mouth.
>It heads straight for Lost Name.
*Scream*
Lost Name!
Ughhh... Aaaaaaagh....
>The smoke enters Lost Name's body.
Resistance is futile. Now, you will learn to obey.
*Groan*
I am your master. Heed my command.
Eliminate these Dx2s.
